item.title: Erin Andrews Opens Up About Cancer Diagnosis: Get The Details!
Holy Cow, This Pinocchio Game Looks Like The Bloodborne Sequel Weve Always Wanted
item.description: South Korean developer Round8 Studio has shown off gameplay for its Souls-like game Lies of P. If you missed out on Lies of P’s announcement, it’s a Souls-like based on the story of Pinocchio. The response to the announcement was generally “it’s a Souls-like based on what?” but the gameplay shown honestly looks pretty good. The game seems like it’s more inspired by Bloodborne than Dark Souls, with fast-paced combat and a more Victorian setting.

item.title: Bradley Cooper Closes Eyes During Rare Interview With Emma Stone Hollywood Life
item.description: Bradley Cooper revealed that sometimes he likes to close his eyes and just focus on his thoughts during an “Actors on Actors” interview with Emma Stone for Variety on Friday, December 8. As The Hangover star, 48, shut his eyes to ask Emma, 35, a question, she called him out for shutting his eyes. The Poor Things actress couldn’t help but laugh at her former Aloha co-star. As Bradley began to ask Emma a question about her “immense talent,” he shut his eyes, seemingly to focus on his thoughts, and the Easy A star quickly noticed the habit and asked him a little bit about it.

item.title: Who are the Stars of OWN'S 'Love & Marriage Huntsville?'
item.description: Tyler Perry took the OWN network to new heights when he landed a deal to produce drama series for the once-struggling cable network years ago. The Haves and the Have Nots became the network’s staple show, putting Oprah Winfrey’s network in the top spot in viewership for that time period The network has continued to produce original programming with both scripted series and reality television series. Their latest hit, Love & Marriage Huntsville, has become one of the network’s most-watched reality shows.
